# Frontend Design Patterns Rules

## 1. Container / Presentational Pattern

- Container components handle state and logic
- Presentational components handle UI rendering only
- Do not mix logic and UI in the same component unless trivial

---

## 2. Custom Hooks Pattern

- Shared logic must be extracted into custom hooks
- Hooks must be reusable and side-effect aware
- Hooks must not directly manipulate UI

---

## 3. Adapter Pattern

- Use adapters to normalize external API data
- UI components must never depend on raw API response shapes
- Data must be transformed before reaching UI layer

---

## 4. Compound Components Pattern

- Use compound components for complex UI systems
- Components must remain composable and flexible
- Avoid deeply nested prop drilling

---

## 5. Composition Over Inheritance

- Prefer composition for UI reuse
- Avoid inheritance-based UI abstractions

---

## 6. Reusability Rule
- Components must be reusable by default unless explicitly domain-specific